<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Rails Javascript POC</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1">
    <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
    <%= csp_meta_tag %>

    <!-- Bootstrap core CSS -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-1BmE4kWBq78iYhFldvKuhfTAU6auU8tT94WrHftjDbrCEXSU1oBoqyl2QvZ6jIW3" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track': 'reload' %>
    <%= javascript_include_tag 'scaffold', 'data-turbolinks-track': 'reload' %>
  </head>

  <body>
  
    <%= render 'layouts/navigation' %>

    <div class="container-fluid mt-4">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-8 col-sm-12">
          <% if notice %>
          <div class="alert alert-success" role="alert"><%= notice %></div>
          <% end %>
          <%= yield %>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4 col-sm-12">
          <h3>The Rails Scaffold example with (almost) no javascript</h3>
          <p>This is a straight forward vanilla version of rails generated with scaffold from the command line. It's sort of like the control for an experiment. The only javascript included for this is rails-ujs, which is loaded via sprockets. I added bootstrap via CDN, and I added a little HTML/CSS to the buttons.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
